{# 
    Font (<font>)
    ===========================================================================

    Defines font, color, and size for text. Note that the <font> element is
    deprecated in HTML5 and should not be used. Consider using CSS for styling
    instead.

    Variables:
    - `font_size`: The size of the font. Defaults to "3".
    - `font_color`: The color of the font. Defaults to "black".
    - `font_face`: The face (font family) of the font. Defaults to "Arial".
    - `font_text`: The text to be displayed with the specified font settings. Defaults to "Sample text".

    Notes:
    - The `| e` filter is used to escape any special characters in the variables to prevent XSS attacks.

    Links:
    - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/font
    - https://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_font.asp

#}

<font 
    size="{{ font_size | default('3') | e }}" 
    color="{{ font_color | default('black') | e }}" 
    face="{{ font_face | default('Arial') | e }}"
>
    {{ font_text | default('Sample text') | e }}
</font>
